Class CSJSparseEqnDoubleImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.interpss.core.sparse.impl.AbstractSparseEquation<ISparseEqnSolver>
      • com.interpss.core.sparse.impl.AbstractSparseEqnDoubleImpl
        • com.interpss.core.sparse.impl.csj.CSJSparseEqnDoubleImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ISparseEquation, ISparseEqnDouble

    public class CSJSparseEqnDoubleImpl
extends AbstractSparseEqnDoubleImpl
    CSJ Sparse Equation of data type double for solving the [A]X=B problem. To outside, the index number is from 0 to n-1. When [A] is a square matrix, LU decomposition method is used to solve the eqn When [A] is a non-square matrix, QR decomposition method is used to provide a Least Square or Weighted Least Square solution
